<br>
Many people act like the only way to &quot;fix&quot; CD is to increase its damage.<br>
<br>
My blademaster is 45 now and I'm pretty happy with my damage (although I sure as heck wouldn't mind a nice little damage boost).<br>
<br>
The fix I'd really like to see is to make celtic dual styles actually useful.  At this point, the only styles I'm using (and planning to use all the way through 50) from CD are the ones based off of evade, since blunt doesn't have a chain for that.  Blunt syles beat out CD styles in every other respect.<br>
<br>
Also, I personally find it very funny that the CD detaunt is not only the second in a chain, but the chain is back positional (Yay, I can detaunt a mob that isn't even attacking me!) and adds a high damage bonus (Oh wait no, I can't detaunt it at all!).  I'd love to hear Mythic's reasoning behind that style. :P<br>
<br>
What I would like to see is some unity from the Blademaster community to get our styles fixed before we start asking for increased damage from those styles.  Even if Mythic does increase how much damage they do, they'll still have no useful style effects on them.  I think giving us a useful style line instead of the current CD would help the class a lot more than people seem to think.  Heck, I think it would help more than the increased damage it seems most people are asking for.<br>
<br>
Damage isn't everything.<br>
<br>
So my simple request from this post is to see some unity from all the blademasters to get one thing done before everything else:  Make CD useful.  Stop asking for increased damage and just get our line flat out fixed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skorj>Skorj</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#000000>(12/26/02 10:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=69.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Simple Request</span><hr size=1> I dont want anything except more damage.  I picked the BM at retail, because he sounded like the Hibernian class with the most flat-out melee damage and no timered abilities or tricks or spells.<br>
